St. Thomas
In reply to this message
If the container is plastic definitely don't want to use it. Even if it is glass though, and open container like that will suck all the air into the mix and oxidize the food. The ideal way to blend is fill a ball jar up as high as you can with the food you want to blend, but the blender cap and blades on, turn it upside down and blend it that way. This way very little oxygen gets mixed in with the food.
